quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  38,62,"And they said, “What is it with us that we do not see men whom we used to count among the <span class=""h"">villains?</span>"
  38,63,"<span class=""h"">Did we take them with mockery<sup foot_note=""81007"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, or have our sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>swerved from them?"
  38,64,"Indeed, that is certainly true: the disputing among the inhabitants of the Fire."
  38,65,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Indeed, I am only a forewarner, for there is no god except Allah—the One, the Subduer,"
  38,66,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, the Almighty, the Forgiver.”"
  38,67,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “It is a great tiding"
  38,68,"which you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>disregard."
  38,69,"I have had no knowledge of the Highest Assembly as they disputed."
  38,70,"It is only revealed to <span class=""h"">me</span><span class=""h"">that<sup foot_note=""81008"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>I am an evident warner.”"
  38,71,"Recall when Your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord said to the angels, “Indeed, I am creating a human being from clay."
  38,72,"So when I have formed him and breathed into him of My spirit, fall prostrate before him."
  38,73,"So the angels fell prostrate, all of them, entirely—"
  38,74,"but not Iblis{1}; he acted arrogantly and became one of the deniers.",footnotes:1:Iblis is another name of Satan or Shaytan.
  38,75,"He said, “O Iblis, what prevented you from prostrating before what I created with My Own hands? Have you acted arrogantly, or have you become one of the exalted?”"
  38,76,"He said, “I am better than him; You created me from fire and created him from clay.”"
  38,77,"He said, “Then get out of it, for you are indeed an outcast!"
  38,78,"And indeed, My curse is upon you until the Day of Recompense.”"
  38,79,"He said, “My Lord, then reprieve me until the day they are resurrected.”"
  38,80,"He said, “Then indeed, you are of those reprieved"
  38,81,"until the Day of the Time Appointed.”"
  38,82,"He said, “Then, by Your majesty, I will most surely delude them all,"
  38,83,"except for your <span class=""h"">sincere chosen{1} </span>servants among them.”",footnotes:1:Ibn Kathir, Abu ʻAmr, Ibn ʻAmer and Yaʻqub read it as: “. . . except for your sincere servants among them.”
